The paper deals with optimization problems related to discrete metrics, which are often studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of submodularity is a common technique in these areas, as well as in information theory (cs.IT) and social networks (cs.SI).
